vegetable sheep
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number: 1
Definition:a cushion-like plant Raoulia spp, growing in alpine and subalpine areas [that from a distance looks like a sheep and is a distraction to musterers].
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Flag: Farm Words
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
See:mountain-sheep
Pronunciation:
Notes: incl attrib: vegetable sheep plant
